The paper presents a path planning algorithm based on Deep Reinforcement Learning (DRL) for mobile robots navigating in unknown environments. The algorithm uses raw laser data and odometry information to navigate without relying on a map. The paper also discusses the use of a reward function shaped based on the online knowledge of the map of the training environment, obtained using grid-based Rao-Blackwellized particle filter, to enhance the obstacle awareness of the agent. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the following arXiv CS sub-categories: 
- cs.RO (Robotics)
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence)
- cs.LG (Machine Learning)
- cs.CV (Computer Vision)
- cs.SY (Systems and Control)
